{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
'''Col<U+00E9>gio Santa Maria''' is a [[Roman Catholic Church|Catholic]] secondary school founded in [[S<U+00E3>o Paulo]], Brazil by the [[Sisters of the Holy Cross]] in 1947. It is considered one of the best [[Paulist]] schools by ''Veja'' magazine.

In the past, it was a girls-only school. 

